re."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Eustace","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Old French form of the Late Greek names <i>Eustakhios</i> and <i>Eustathios</i>. These were evidently of separate origin, the former derived from <i>eu</i> ‘well, good’ + <i>stakhys</i> ‘grapes’, the latter from <i>eu</i> + <i>stēnai</i> ‘to stand’. However, the tradition is very confused. The name was introduced in this form to Britain by the Normans, among whom it was popular as a result of the fame of  St Eustace , a Norman nobleman who was said to have been converted to Christianity by the vision of a crucifix between the antlers of the stag he was hunting."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Eustace d'Arderne was born in 1165, in Watford, Northamptonshire, England, his father, Eustace d'Arderne, was 25 and his mother, Agnes of Watford, was 20. He married Hawysia in 1190, in Watford, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. He died in 1213, in Watford, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 48."},"et":{"1165–1213":"1165–1213","1170–1213":"1170–1213","1190–1221":"1190–1221","1190–1230":"1190–1230","1193–Male":"1193–Surnud","1140–1213":"1140–1213","1145–1200":"1145–1200","1190":"1190","about 1193":"umbes 1193","1213":"1213","1200":"1200","1145":"1145","1221":"1221","1165":"1165","1230":"1230","1140":"1140","1193":"1193","1170":"1170","Watford, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Watford, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Arden, Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Alvanley, Cheshire, England":"Alvanley, Cheshire, England","Woolcombe, Dorset, England":"Woolcombe, Dorset, England","Aldford, Cheshire, England":"Aldford, Cheshire, England","Watford, Northamptonshire, England":"Watford, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1165–1213":"1